* Taishō 4 (1915) March 12 - shinsen-heihaku-ryō kyōshinsha

=== Precinct shrines ===
Merged before Meiji.
* Kubo Inari Shrine<ref name="Kōtaijinja origin">Commemorative booklet for the 62nd Ise Grand Shrine rebuilding, ''Kōtaijinja Origin''</ref>  
Merged in Meiji 41. "Kōtaijinja" was returned in Shōwa 21 (1946) to its former site in Kubo at strong local request.
* Kubo Kōtaijinja (deity) Ōhirume-no-Muchi-no-Mikoto<ref name="Kōtaijinja origin"/>
* Aza-Miya Niu-sha
* Aza-Miya Inari-sha
: subordinate shrine of Aza-Miya Niu-sha
